<h1 id='files-api-deprecated-1'><span id=files-api-deprecated></span>Files API (deprecated)</h1><h2 id='introduction-1'><span id=introduction></span>Introduction</h2><h3 id='a-name-file-model-a-file-model-1'><span id=a-name-file-model-a-file-model></span><a name="file-model"></a> File model</h3>
<p>Every file attached to some entity (Offer, Reward, Offer Collection) follows the file schema and is defined like this:</p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Key</th>
<th>Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>url</td>
<td>URL</td>
<td>Link to the file</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>width</td>
<td>integer</td>
<td>Image width</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>height</td>
<td>integer</td>
<td>Image height</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>kind</td>
<td>string</td>
<td>File kind identifier (e.x. <code>offer_default</code>), see <a href="#file-kinds">Standard file kinds</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>size_type</td>
<td>string</td>
<td>e.x. <code>base</code>, see: <a href="#file-sizes">File sizes</a></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h3 id='a-name-file-schema-a-file-schema-1'><span id=a-name-file-schema-a-file-schema></span><a name="file-schema"></a> File schema</h3>
<p>File schema defines a list of files kinds available in the Loyalty club.
Each file kind is also available in multiple sizes.</p>

<p>The schema may get retrieved with <a href="#get-file-schema">Files&gt; Get schema</a> endpoint.</p>

<blockquote>
<p>Example loyalty club file schema</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight json tab-json"><code><span class="p">{</span><span class="w">
